snippet: Federal prosecutors looked into the activities of the Working Families Party and found no whiff of wrongdoing, but the organization cannot seem to get out from under the microscope.
abstract: Michael Powell Gotham column holds that federal prosecutors looked into the campaign activities of the Working Families Party arising from a 2009 City Council Race on Staten Island and found no wrongdoing, but observes that the organization cannot seem to get out from under the microscope.
lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors looked into the activities of the Working Families Party and found no whiff of wrongdoing, but the organization cannot seem to get out from under the microscope.

headline.print_headline: A Liberal Party Faces Inquiries Without End
headline.seo: For Working Families Party, Inquiries Without End
headline.main: A Liberal Party Faces Inquiries Without End
